    <text id="B0082T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Brown informs Jackson about the status of the case between John Brent and John
                    Miller.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Thomas <orig reg="P.">J.</orig> Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="01-02">January 2nd</date>
                        <name type="place">Near Brownsburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Your letter of <unclear>enquiry</unclear> was duly received concerning John Brent
                        <abbr expan="colored">col.</abbr> against <unclear>Joh.</unclear> Miller.
                    The case was duly tried and upon John's our acknowledgements. Miller brought him
                    in debt. Not having the docket I cannot give a full statement as there is two of
                    us sets together and renders up judgements time about.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>Daniel Brown <abbr expan="Justice of the Peace">J.P.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
